26 LC 112 4312
House Resolution 46EX
By: Representatives Reeves of the 99th, Hong of the 103rd, and Clark of the 100th
A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing and commending the Broad Street Concert Band of Sugar Hill; and for other
2 purposes.
3 WHEREAS, the Broad Street Concert Band of Sugar Hill has become a treasured cultural
4 asset within the City of Sugar Hill and throughout Gwinnett County, enriching the lives of
5 residents through musical excellence, community engagement, and a steadfast commitment
6 to the performing arts; and
7 WHEREAS, the band is composed of dedicated volunteer musicians of diverse ages,
8 backgrounds, and professions who unite around a shared passion for music and service,
9 demonstrating the power of the arts to build community and foster connection; and
10 WHEREAS, through concerts, civic performances, seasonal celebrations, and partnerships
11 with local organizations and the City of Sugar Hill, the Broad Street Concert Band has
12 provided countless opportunities for families, students, and seniors to experience high quality
13 live music close to home; and
14 WHEREAS, the band's presence has strengthened Sugar Hill's identity as a vibrant, creative,
15 and culturally rich city, complementing the community's investment in the arts and
H. R. 46EX
- 1 -

26 LC 112 4312
16 contributing to the continued growth of the E Center, the Eagle Theatre, and the broader
17 downtown arts district; and
18 WHEREAS, the Broad Street Concert Band has served as an ambassador for Sugar Hill,
19 representing the city with professionalism and pride while inspiring young musicians,
20 supporting local schools, and encouraging lifelong participation in the arts; and
21 WHEREAS, strong communities are built not only through infrastructure and commerce but
22 also through the shared experiences that bring people together, and the Broad Street Concert
23 Band has played a meaningful role in strengthening the social and cultural fabric of Sugar
24 Hill; and
25 WHEREAS, it is fitting and proper to honor organizations whose contributions uplift the
26 spirit of their communities and reflect the values of service, creativity, and civic pride.
27 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
28 the members of this body recognize and commend the Broad Street Concert Band of Sugar
29 Hill for its positive impact on the Sugar Hill community and extend sincere best wishes for
30 its continued success and growth.
31 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
32 and directed to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to the
33 Broad Street Concert Band of Sugar Hill.
